Ratio of [latex]P_{S B}[/latex] to [latex]P_{C}[/latex] is [latex]
\begin{array}{l}
\quad P_{S B}={P}_{C}{\mu}^{2} \\
\begin{array}{l}
\therefore \quad \frac{P_{S B}}{P_{C}}=\frac{\mu^{2}}{2} \\
\text { and }\left(\frac{P_{S B}}{P_{C}}\right)_{1}=\frac{\mu_{1}^{2}}{2} \\
\left(\frac{P_{S B}}{P_{C}}\right)_{2}=\frac{\mu_{2}^{2}}{2} \\
\text { where, } \quad\left(\frac{P_{S B}}{P_{C}}\right)_{2}=\frac{\mu_{2}^{2}}{2} \\
\text { hence } \frac{\left(P_{S B} / P_{C}\right)_{1}}{\left(P_{S B} / P_{C}\right)_{2}}=\frac{1}{4} \\
\left(\frac{P_{S B}}{P_{C}}\right)_{2}=4\left(\frac{P_{S B}}{P_{C}}\right)_{1}
\end{array}
\end{array}[/latex] Four times.
